  "name": "Morrison COU2 — VAD hemolysis credibility assessment (NC-8 clean)",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under ventricular assist device (VAD) conditions. COU2 evaluates whether the computational model can predict absolute hemolysis levels for a Class III VAD device at Model Risk Level 5. This package is a negative-control clean specimen: the ContextOfUse declares both hasOperatingEnvelope and hasApplicabilityConstraint as structured inline objects with concrete quantitative bounds, and all validation activities are demonstrated to cover the declared envelope densely. All 13 credibility factors are assessed with achievedLevel meeting or exceeding requiredLevel. Decision: Accepted.",
