      "type": "ApplicabilityConstraint",
      "name": "VAD applicability constraint — in-scope domain",
      "description": "Model applicability is restricted to: (1) centrifugal pump geometries with specific speed Ns between 800 and 1800 (dimensionless), matching the FDA generic pump family; (2) Newtonian-equivalent Reynolds numbers Re 3000–80000 at the impeller inlet; (3) single-pass hemolysis index (HI) predictions only — recirculation-loop cumulative HI is outside scope; (4) aqueous glycerol blood analogue or porcine blood as test fluid; (5) steady-state operating points only — transient ramp conditions are excluded. Extrapolation beyond these bounds requires a new credibility assessment."
    }
